  "text": "The formation of a limited amount of xanthophylls in flowers of wf indicates the existence of low-level b-ring hydroxylation activity that can be provided by CRTR-B1, which is expressed at a low level, or by a third b-carotene hydroxylase. Another possible source of b-carotene hydroxylation in wf flowers is a residual b-carotene hydroxylation activity by the e-ring hydroxylase that has been suggested [CITATION_1] .",
